          <avActivityHighlights>In some localities increase in avalanche danger as a consequence of warming during the day and solar radiation.</avActivityHighlights>
          <avActivityComment>&lt;br/&gt; Especially adjacent to ridgelines and in gullies and bowls: The fresh snow as well as all the wind slabs can be released by a single winter sport participant. &lt;br/&gt; Backcountry touring calls for careful route selection. &lt;br/&gt; &lt;br/&gt; In steep rocky terrain and on sunny slopes occasionally large natural avalanches are possible as a consequence of warming during the day and solar radiation.</avActivityComment>
          <snowpackStructureComment>20 to 30 cm of snow, and up to 50 cm in some localities, fell on Sunday. Especially in the areas bordering Piedmont. The wind was light to moderate adjacent to ridgelines. &lt;br/&gt; &lt;br/&gt; Over a wide area new snow is lying on the soft surface of an old snowpack. Or on crusts. &lt;br/&gt; Towards its surface, the snowpack is weak in some cases; its surface consists of faceted crystals. Weak layers exist in the snowpack in particular on steep shady slopes. &lt;br/&gt; Especially adjacent to ridgelines in all aspects: Over a wide area snow depths vary greatly, depending on the infuence of the wind.</snowpackStructureComment>
          <tendencyComment>The weather conditions will facilitate a gradual strengthening of the near-surface layers in particular on sunny slopes.</tendencyComment>
